The number $N=2026$ lies on a spiral laid out on a hexagonal grid. We first need to determine which layer $K$ this number belongs to.
The total number of cells up to Layer $K$ is given by $S_K = 1 + 3K(K+1)$.

1. Determine the layer $K$:
We estimate $K$: $3K^2 \approx 2026$, $K^2 \approx 675.3$, so $K \approx 26$.
$S_{25} = 1 + 3(25)(26) = 1 + 1950 = 1951$.
$S_{26} = 1 + 3(26)(27) = 1 + 2106 = 2107$.
Since $1951 < 2026 \le 2107$, $N=2026$ is in Layer $K=26$.

2. Determine the side $j$ and position $p$ within the layer:
Layer 26 has $L_{26} = 6K = 6(26) = 156$ numbers, starting from $N_{start, 26} = 1952$.
The length of each side is $K=26$.
$m = N - S_{25} = 2026 - 1951 = 75$.
Side 1 ends at $C_1 = 1951 + 26 = 1977$.
Side 2 ends at $C_2 = 1977 + 26 = 2003$.
Side 3 starts at $N_{start, 26, 3} = 2004$ and ends at $C_3 = 2003 + 26 = 2029$.
Since $2004 \le 2026 \le 2029$, $N$ is on Side $j=3$.
The position $p$ within Side 3 is $p = 2026 - 2003 = 23$. ($1 \le p \le 26$).

3. Determine the 6 neighbors:
For a number $N$ located on Side $j$ of Layer $K$ (where $1 < p < K$), the six neighbors are generally given by:
a) $N-1$ and $N+1$ (Layer $K$).
b) Two neighbors in Layer $K-1$: $M_1$ and $M_2$.
c) Two neighbors in Layer $K+1$: $O_1$ and $O_2$.

For $N=2026$:
a) $N_1 = 2025$ and $N_2 = 2027$.

b) Inward neighbors (Layer $K-1 = 25$). $L_{25} = 150$.
We need to find the starting index of Side 3 in $L_{25}$:
$S_{24} = 1 + 3(24)(25) = 1 + 1800 = 1801$.
$N_{start, 25, 3} = 1801 + 2(25) + 1 = 1852$.
The cells $M$ corresponding to position $p=23$ on Side 3 of $L_{25}$ are:
$M_1 = N_{start, 25, 3} + p - 1 = 1852 + 22 = 1874$.
Since $p>1$, the other inward neighbor is $M_2 = M_1 - 1 = 1873$.

c) Outward neighbors (Layer $K+1 = 27$). $L_{27} = 6(27) = 162$.
$S_{26} = 2107$.
$N_{start, 27, 3} = 2107 + 2(27) + 1 = 2107 + 55 = 2162$.
The cells $O$ corresponding to position $p=23$ on Side 3 of $L_{27}$ are:
$O_1 = N_{start, 27, 3} + p - 1 = 2162 + 22 = 2184$.
Since $p<K=26$, the other outward neighbor is $O_2 = O_1 + 1 = 2185$.

4. Calculate the sum:
Sum $= N_1 + N_2 + M_1 + M_2 + O_1 + O_2$
Sum $= 2025 + 2027 + 1874 + 1873 + 2184 + 2185$
Sum $= 4052 + 3747 + 4369$
Sum $= 12168$.
